<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12214f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12214f">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12214f"> 214(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Ghosts</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Enfin, &agrave; l&apos;intime relation des h&eacute;ros et des f&ecirc;tes conviennent leurs caract&egrave;res de morts, car les f&ecirc;tes sont des dates du culte fun&eacute;raire et, s&apos;il est des esprits dont la part qu&apos;ils prennent aux f&ecirc;tes soit express&eacute;ment mentionn&eacute;e, ce sont les esprits des morts. <br><font color="green">[Finally, the intimate relationship between heroes and festivals corresponds with the fact that they are dead, because the festivals are the dates of the funerary cult and, if there are spirits whose role in the festival is explicitly mentioned, they are the <mark>spirits of the dead</mark>.]</font> <small> Stefan Czarnowski, <a name="SCSP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SCSP"><cite title="source">Le culte des h&eacute;ros et ses conditions sociale: saint Patrick, h&eacute;ros nationale de l'Irlande</cite></a> (1919) LXXIII</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
